    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix task allocation and uninitialized variable usage in RRC data indication functions\n\n### Summary\nThe RRC data indication functions in both LTE and NR UE implementations contained incorrect task allocation logic and used uninitialized variables, causing unpredictable behavior during RRC message processing. Specifically, the `rrc_data_ind_ue` function was using conditional task allocation that didn't match its UE-specific context, and several functions were referencing uninitialized `sdu_size` variables in log messages and comparisons.\n\nThese issues could lead to segmentation faults or incorrect buffer handling when processing RRC messages from the PDCP layer, particularly during initial access procedures where proper task messaging is critical.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/L2_interface_ue.c`: \n  * Fixed task allocation in `rrc_data_ind_ue` to use fixed UE task IDs instead of conditional logic\n  * Corrected uninitialized variable usage in `mac_rrc_data_ind_ue` for CCCH and MCCH message processing\n  * Made buffer size handling consistent throughout the function\n\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/L2_interface_ue.c`:\n  * Fixed uninitialized variable usage in `nr_mac_rrc_data_ind_ue` for BCCH and SBCCH message processing\n  * Updated log messages to use correct parameter values for buffer size comparisons\n\n"
}